DOC.brief_summary: The purpose of this follow-up study is to collect the outcome and safety of FTET cycles after the embryos are cryopreserved in P06029 (NCT01144416). P06029 was a study in which a single injection of corifollitropin alfa (SCH 900962) was compared with daily recombinant follicle stimulating hormone (recFSH) injections in women aged 35 to 42 years undergoing controlled ovarian stimulation (COS) prior to in vitro fertilization (IVF) or intracytoplasmic sperm injection (ICSI).
DOC.brief_title: Frozen-thawed Embryo Transfer (FTET) Cycle Follow-up Protocol (P06031)
DOC.criteria: Participant must have provided written informed consent for the trial. Participant must have cryopreserved embryo(s) in trial P06029 (NCT01144416) of which at least one embryo is thawed for use in a subsequent FTET cycle.
